Global Funds Buy Net 19.5 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-25T03:39:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/global-funds-buy-net-19-5-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global funds bought a net 19.5
billion rupees ($437 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, gained 2.5 percent to 976 billion rupees, or 32.9
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign investors bought a net 3.08 billion rupees of
shares in the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary
data given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
